TM.TAX.MANF.BC.ZS-tariffs.def: Binding coverage is the percentage of product lines with an agreed bound rate. Manufactured products are commodities classified in SITC revision 3 sections 5-8 excluding division 68.
TM.TAX.MANF.BC.ZS-tariffs.name: Binding coverage
TM.TAX.MANF.BC.ZS-tariffs.source: World Bank staff estimates using the World Integrated Trade Solution system, based on data from World Trade Organization.

TM.TAX.MANF.BR.ZS-tariffs.def: Simple mean bound rate is the unweighted average of all the lines in the tariff schedule in which bound rates have been set. Manufactured products are commodities classified in SITC revision 3 sections 5-8 excluding division 68.
TM.TAX.MANF.BR.ZS-tariffs.name: Bound rate, simple mean
TM.TAX.MANF.BR.ZS-tariffs.source: World Bank staff estimates using the World Integrated Trade Solution system, based on data from World Trade Organization.

TM.TAX.MANF.IP.ZS-tariffs.def: Share of tariff lines with international peaks is the share of lines in the tariff schedule with tariff rates that exceed 15 percent. Manufactured products are commodities classified in SITC revision 3 sections 5-8 excluding division 68.
TM.TAX.MANF.IP.ZS-tariffs.name: Share of tariff lines with international peaks
TM.TAX.MANF.IP.ZS-tariffs.source: World Bank staff estimates using the World Integrated Trade Solution system, based on data from United Nations Conference on Trade and Development's Trade Analysis and Information System (TRAINS) database.

TM.TAX.MANF.SM.AR.ZS-tariffs.def: Simple mean applied tariff is the unweighted average of effectively applied rates for all products subject to tariffs calculated for all traded goods. Manufactured products are commodities classified in SITC revision 3 sections 5-8 excluding division 68.
TM.TAX.MANF.SM.AR.ZS-tariffs.name: Tariff rate, applied, simple mean
TM.TAX.MANF.SM.AR.ZS-tariffs.source: World Bank staff estimates using the World Integrated Trade Solution system, based on data from United Nations Conference on Trade and Development's Trade Analysis and Information System (TRAINS) database and the World Trade Organization’s (WTO) Integrated Data Base (IDB) and Consolidated Tariff Schedules (CTS) database.

TM.TAX.MANF.SM.FN.ZS-tariffs.def: Simple mean most favored nation tariff rate is the unweighted average of most favored nation rates for all products subject to tariffs calculated for all traded goods. TM.TAX.MANF.SM.FN.ZS-tariffs.source: World Bank staff estimates using the World Integrated Trade Solution system, based on data from United Nations Conference on Trade and Development's Trade Analysis and Information System (TRAINS) database and the World Trade Organization’s (WTO) Integrated Data Base (IDB) and Consolidated Tariff Schedules (CTS) database.

TM.TAX.MANF.SR.ZS-tariffs.def: Share of tariff lines with specific rates is the share of lines in the tariff schedule that are set on a per unit basis or that combine ad valorem and per unit rates. Manufactured products are commodities classified in SITC revision 3 sections 5-8 excluding division 68.
TM.TAX.MANF.SR.ZS-tariffs.name: Share of tariff lines with specific rates
TM.TAX.MANF.SR.ZS-tariffs.source: World Bank staff estimates using the World Integrated Trade Solution system, based on data from United Nations Conference on Trade and Development's Trade Analysis and Information System (TRAINS) database.

TM.TAX.MANF.WM.AR.ZS-tariffs.source: World Bank staff estimates using the World Integrated Trade Solution system, based on data from United Nations Conference on Trade and Development's Trade Analysis and Information System (TRAINS) database and the World Trade Organization’s (WTO) Integrated Data Base (IDB) and Consolidated Tariff Schedules (CTS) database.
